post_text: Great news for our USD 364 families. We received approval this morning for our waiver/request to extend the USDA's Summer Food Service Program for school aged children. This program will start Tuesday, September 8th. It will allow both breakfast and lunch to be FREE for ALL students. The waiver to serve free meals goes until 12/31/2020 or until USDA funds run out. Please join this program. Families choosing to take advantage of such programs helps family budgets...which in the end helps our kids be more successful in school. Again, all families automatically qualify.

post_text: Please join us as we strive to deliver a complete message regarding how school will look as we begin this new school year. We are asking our local community to gather behind your local schools as we are ready to begin school again. Thank you in advance for getting behind this plan, encouraging your kids in this "different" time, and picking up the partnership between home and school that we had last spring. We are excited to be teaching again and hope families can rest assured in our efforts. This will allow parents to transition back from teaching their kids at home as we called on them to do last spring, toward managing work and home. We are looking forward to many good stories coming home to mom and dad about learning, exploring, and growing. Please view this video to hear more about our plan that was designed just for USD 364 Marysville Schools. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BLhHb9lPrtc&feature=youtu.be

post_text: We are getting ready for a great 2020-2021 school year. Please review our reopening plan. We are asking our community and families to get behind these plans since they allow us to get our kids back to as normal a setting as possible for now. Our response code system is based on four levels: Checkered, Green, Yellow, and Red. We will begin on Yellow with hopes that we can move to green. However, we are ready to make a few sacrifices to get our kids back into school. A HUGE thank you goes out to a great team of 364 administrators and teachers for designing this plan to fit our schools specifically. Thank you for your support. See you at enrollment next week. https://docs.google.com/document/d/1WakV5Ihjr8QmY10t08KBA9SPVeotSaIo9uttFj14Iz8/edit?usp=sharing

text: Parents of a Marysville Jr/Sr High School Student if you would like to observe your student in Canvas please follow the instructions in this short tutorial video.

post_text:
Parents of a Marysville Jr/Sr High School Student if you would like to observe your student in Canvas please create a pairing code using the following instructions. If you would like to see a short video tutorial please see the next post.

Observing your students in Canvas -

1. Have your student log into Canvas
2. Click on their account (left hand side)
3. Click on Settings
4. Click “Pair with an Observer”
5. Copy the pairing code that is generated
6. Student Log out
7. Click on “Parent of a Canvas User”
8. Fill in Your Name, Email, Create a Password, and copy the pairing code that was generated
9. Start Participating

For parents with multiple students.
While you are logged into your parent account, Click account, click Observing, and then use your other students pairing codes to add them there.
